Question: My spouse, who was an ECB staff member, recently passed away while in
  service. What benefits apply with regard to salary continuation and
  to our return to our country of origin?
Example answer: In the event of the death of a staff member, payment of their salary
  and allowances is extended for three months. Where termination of
  service is caused by death, the resettlement benefits — coverage of
  travel-related expenses and removal of personal belongings, together
  with a resettlement allowance equal to 200% of the monthly basic
  salary for staff entitled to a household allowance or 100% otherwise
  — are paid, under the conditions laid down in the Staff Rules, to
  the surviving spouse or recognised partner or, in their absence, to
  the deceased staff member's dependent children. (ECB Conditions of
  Employment, pages 12, 19)
